Klaus Herrmanns wrote:
>
>Of course, if we reintroduce unemployment benefit, this will mean that
>people (like me) who hold a single office with a salary of 1 BOS do
>not receive any reward for their work. Now in my case that's not too
>bad really, because I am certainly not overworking myself as
>ambassador. But with plots half introduced now I, for one, would
>prefer to make plots functional soon, and give non-officers a way to
>earn real money. Unemployment benefits are, IMHO, just a makeshift
>tool to keep non-officers alive until plots are running.

A couple of remarks. You seem to have forgotten that unemployment
benefits are expressed in terms of the BOS: they are half the BOS
to be precise. So Officers will always have a relative VT-income
advantage with respect to the unemployed, which is probably as it
should be.

Secondly, I think we should regard the necessity of halving the BOS
as an indication that Officers are currently overpaid.

